author_ssm: Rebecca Altermatt, Meaghan Dwyer, Brendan Dolan
unittitle_ssm: Archives of Irish America Collection of Irish Institute of New York
abstract_ssm: The Irish Institute of New York, originally known as the American Irish Feis Institute, is a non-profit organization dedicated to cultural and philanthropic endeavors since 1950. The collection consists of meeting minutes, correspondence, annual dinner programs and speeches, brochures, financial reports, and committee information.
